{"type":"message","id":"e4c22990","parentId":"43e59f4a","timestamp":"2026-02-28T09:30:27.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"我看到了很多最近的issues！让我找一个适合新手的issue。从列表中我看到有几个标记为\"bug\"的问题，但没有看到明确的\"good first issue\"标签。让我检查一下issue #29617，这个看起来相对简单：\n\n**Issue #29617**: \"Media parser: accept `MEDIA :` directives with whitespace around colon\"\n\n这是一个关于媒体解析器的小改进，需要让解析器能够接受冒号周围有空格的MEDIA指令。这看起来是一个很好的入门级任务！\n\n让我先查看这个issue的详细内容：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_79eae57351944fefa148ff0e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh issue view 29617 -R openclaw/openclaw"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":16335,"output":158,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16493,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772271018336}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b922b19","parentId":"e4c22990","timestamp":"2026-02-28T09:30:27.970Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_79eae57351944fefa148ff0e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"title:\tMedia parser: accept `MEDIA :` directives with whitespace around colon\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\ttheos2node\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t29617\n--\n## Summary\n\nFixed a parser mismatch where `MEDIA : /tmp/file.png` was treated as plain text by the shared media-directive parser, even though other parts of the codebase already document and accept lenient whitespace around the colon.\n\n## Repro\n\nBefore the fix:\n\n- `splitMediaFromOutput('MEDIA : /tmp/file.png')` returned plain text instead of `mediaUrls: ['/tmp/file.png']`\n- tool-result media extraction also missed `MEDIA : ...` lines because it relies on the same shared parser\n\nAt the same time, the loader already accepts this format:\n\n- `loadWebMedia('  MEDIA :  /tmp/file.png', ...)` works\n- the reply prompt guidance explicitly says spaces are OK for inline `MEDIA:` usage\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe shared parser in `src/media/parse.ts` was inconsistent in two places:\n\n- the token regex only matched `MEDIA:`\n- the line-start guard only accepted lines starting with `MEDIA:`\n\nThat meant lenient whitespace variants never reached the existing parsing logic.\n\n## Fix\n\nUpdated the shared parser to accept optional whitespace around the colon consistently:\n\n- `MEDIA:`\n- `MEDIA :`\n- `  MEDIA :  /tmp/file.png`\n\nThe change is intentionally narrow:\n\n- only the regex and line-start gate were widened\n- existing prose protection remains covered by tests so `MEDIA : not-a-path` still stays as text\n\n## Validation\n\nAdded regression coverage for:\n\n- direct parser support for whitespace variants\n- tool-result media extraction support for whitespace variants\n- non-token prose remaining unchanged\n\nValidated with:\n\n- `pnpm vitest run src/media/parse.test.ts`\n- `pnpm vitest run src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.tools.media.test.ts`\n- `pnpm vitest run src/web/media.test.ts`\n\n## Files\n\n- `src/media/parse.ts`\n- `src/media/parse.test.ts`\n- `src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.tools.media.test.ts`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":948,"aggregated":"title:\tMedia parser: accept `MEDIA :` directives with whitespace around colon\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\ttheos2node\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t29617\n--\n## Summary\n\nFixed a parser mismatch where `MEDIA : /tmp/file.png` was treated as plain text by the shared media-directive parser, even though other parts of the codebase already document and accept lenient whitespace around the colon.\n\n## Repro\n\nBefore the fix:\n\n- `splitMediaFromOutput('MEDIA : /tmp/file.png')` returned plain text instead of `mediaUrls: ['/tmp/file.png']`\n- tool-result media extraction also missed `MEDIA : ...` lines because it relies on the same shared parser\n\nAt the same time, the loader already accepts this format:\n\n- `loadWebMedia('  MEDIA :  /tmp/file.png', ...)` works\n- the reply prompt guidance explicitly says spaces are OK for inline `MEDIA:` usage\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe shared parser in `src/media/parse.ts` was inconsistent in two places:\n\n- the token regex only matched `MEDIA:`\n- the line-start guard only accepted lines starting with `MEDIA:`\n\nThat meant lenient whitespace variants never reached the existing parsing logic.\n\n## Fix\n\nUpdated the shared parser to accept optional whitespace around the colon consistently:\n\n- `MEDIA:`\n- `MEDIA :`\n- `  MEDIA :  /tmp/file.png`\n\nThe change is intentionally narrow:\n\n- only the regex and line-start gate were widened\n- existing prose protection remains covered by tests so `MEDIA : not-a-path` still stays as text\n\n## Validation\n\nAdded regression coverage for:\n\n- direct parser support for whitespace variants\n- tool-result media extraction support for whitespace variants\n- non-token prose remaining unchanged\n\nValidated with:\n\n- `pnpm vitest run src/media/parse.test.ts`\n- `pnpm vitest run src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.tools.media.test.ts`\n- `pnpm vitest run src/web/media.test.ts`\n\n## Files\n\n- `src/media/parse.ts`\n- `src/media/parse.test.ts`\n- `src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.tools.media.test.ts`","cwd":"/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/coding/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772271027963}}
